description: This is a mock class for floating remote functions used in testing, created with Google Mock framework. It defines mock methods for remote environment management and error handling functions.

classes.name: floatingRtFunctionsMock
classes.description: Mock class for floating remote functions, providing mock implementations for testing purposes.

methods.name: rtRemoteLocateObject
methods.description: Mocks locating a remote object in the environment.

methods.name: rtEnvironmentGetGlobal
methods.description: Mocks retrieving the global remote environment.

methods.name: rtRemoteShutdown
methods.description: Mocks shutting down a remote environment.

methods.name: rtRemoteProcessSingleItem
methods.description: Mocks processing a single remote item.

methods.name: rtStrError
methods.description: Mocks retrieving a string error message based on an error code.
